<subSubSection id="06B760DBFFF8FFAA4E8F82E0FBC6FEDE" pageId="8" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="4E123350FFF8FFAA4E8F82E0FBC6FEDE" blockId="8.[151,1436,152,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="7CD9EF42FFF8FFAA4E8F82E0FE90FE8D" bold="true" box="[199,344,231,257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="29">Description</emphasis>
. Mature specimens ~ 
<quantity id="89559EB5FFF8FFAA4C1E82EFFD7CFE8E" box="[598,692,232,258]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="600.0">600 µm</quantity>
in length and ~ 
<quantity id="89559EB5FFF8FFAA4D3882EFFC06FE8E" box="[880,974,232,258]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="150.0">150 µm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation id="D6962FD5FFF8FFAA4A6882EFFBB7FE8E" box="[1056,1151,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,255,1538,1562]" captionTargetBox="[266,1321,554,1514]" captionTargetId="figure-199@8.[266,1321,554,1514]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Photomicrographs of living acoel specimens. A. Hofstenia miamia collected from decaying mangrove leaves. B. Hofstenia miamia collected from a bed of Thalassia sp. C. Avagina cf. marci." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5086538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5086538/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="29">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Anterior and posterior ends rounded; posterior end club-shaped (
<figureCitation id="D6962FD5FFF8FFAA4CC78317FD27FEA6" box="[655,751,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,255,1538,1562]" captionTargetBox="[266,1321,554,1514]" captionTargetId="figure-199@8.[266,1321,554,1514]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Photomicrographs of living acoel specimens. A. Hofstenia miamia collected from decaying mangrove leaves. B. Hofstenia miamia collected from a bed of Thalassia sp. C. Avagina cf. marci." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5086538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5086538/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="29">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Body without coloration in transmitted light. Rhabdoid glands not present. Mouth opening on ventral surface, anterior half of body.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="06B760DBFFF8FFAA4E8F8358FF11FE7E" pageId="8" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4E123350FFF8FFAA4E8F8358FF11FE7E" blockId="8.[151,1436,152,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="7CD9EF42FFF8FFAA4E8F8358FEF1FEF5" bold="true" box="[199,313,351,377]" pageId="8" pageNumber="29">Remarks</emphasis>
. Mature specimens of this species were relatively fragile, thereby preventing us from obtaining material suitable for histological sections. We tentatively identify this species as 
<taxonomicName id="89AD48D3FFF8FFAA4A38838FFAD6FE2D" authorityName="Dorjes and Karling" authorityYear="1975" box="[1136,1310,392,417]" class="Acoelomorpha" family="Isodiametridae" genus="Avagina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acoela" pageId="8" pageNumber="29" phylum="Xenacoelomorpha" rank="species" species="marci">
<emphasis id="7CD9EF42FFF8FFAA4A38838FFAD6FE2D" box="[1136,1310,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="29">Avagina marci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its superficial similarity in appearance to 
<taxonomicName id="89AD48D3FFF8FFAA4C1383B7FD77FE45" authorityName="Dorjes and Karling" authorityYear="1975" box="[603,703,432,457]" class="Acoelomorpha" family="Isodiametridae" genus="Avagina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acoela" pageId="8" pageNumber="29" phylum="Xenacoelomorpha" rank="species" species="marci">
<emphasis id="7CD9EF42FFF8FFAA4C1383B7FD77FE45" box="[603,703,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="29">A. marci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well its nearly identical 18S rDNA sequence (unpublished data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
